prompt.user:
Project: {project_name}
Client: {client_name}
Methodology: {methodology}
Service Lines: {service_lines}

Project Type Guidance:
{project_type_guidance}

SOW Summary:
{sow_summary}

Service Line Design Standards:
{standards_context}

HLD Context (use component names already defined in the HLD — diagram must be consistent):
{hld_context}

Generated Requirements Context:
{requirements_context}

Generate the System Architecture Diagram for {project_name}.

RULES:
- Minimum 15 nodes. A 4-box diagram is unacceptable — be granular and specific.
- Every platform must have its own subgraph with at least 3 internal components.
- Use REAL component names from the SOW and HLD context above — not generic placeholders.
- Apply classes with separate `class NodeId className` statements — NEVER inside node labels.
- EVERY single node that appears in the diagram MUST appear in a class statement at the bottom. No node left uncoloured.
- Arrow format: `A -->|label| B` — no `>` after the closing `|`.
- classDef must NOT contain `rx:` — it breaks the Mermaid parser.
- Before finishing, do a self-check: count all node IDs and verify each one appears in a `class` line.
- Do NOT add a "Note:" section. Output ONLY markdown.
